      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No. Telehealth psychology -- delivered by video -- is available from any registered psychologist in NSW, regardless of where their practice is based. The Medicare rebate for telehealth sessions is the same as for in-person sessions (from 1 July 2025: $145.25 with an endorsed clinical psychologist; $98.95 with a registered psychologist). You can access a practitioner based in Parramatta, North Sydney, or anywhere else entirely via telehealth from your home in Newtown, Glebe, Balmain, or Leichhardt. The pool of available practitioners is effectively the entire registered psychology cohort in NSW, not just those based in your suburb."
      }
